Stats is very difficult. It requires hard work and motivation. However, Professor Brand gives you the knowledge you need to do well. It's up to you to do the rest. Read the textbook, do the homework, pay attention, and ask questions. This is by no means an easy class, but you can do well--I finished the class with an A+.

Professor Brand's slides are extremely compact and detailed and demonstrate exactly what you need to know.  Consequently you will not have to spend hours reading the textbook.  However you will need to practice with the problems in the textbook but more importantly do the exercises in the study guide and practice with the old exams.

Prof Brand is an amazing professor, he knows how to teach and goes at a slow enough pace for everyone to understand. stats can be a difficult course, so make sure you attend all classes, re-look over the class material after class, and clarify as you go.
